 <office:body>
  <office:text text:use-soft-page-breaks="true">
   <text:sequence-decls>
    <text:sequence-decl text:display-outline-level="0" text:name="Illustration"/>
    <text:sequence-decl text:display-outline-level="0" text:name="Table"/>
    <text:sequence-decl text:display-outline-level="0" text:name="Text"/>
    <text:sequence-decl text:display-outline-level="0" text:name="Drawing"/>
    <text:sequence-decl text:display-outline-level="0" text:name="Figure"/>
   </text:sequence-decls>
   <text:p text:style-name="P2" loext:marker-style-name="T1"><text:span text:style-name="T1">In May of each year the Shasta Birding Society conducts a bird walk in the McArthur-Burney Falls Memorial State Park. <text:s/>It is always a wonderful tour to the park and the birdlife that lives and visits the park during this time of year. <text:s/>This year <text:s/>on May 30</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">th</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T1"> we walked the west side of Burney Creek, the falls outlook and a bit of the Rim Trail. We then moved to Lake Britton for a look at the lagoon and the northern views of the lake. <text:s/>Here are the Birds we saw and heard on our visit.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P3" loext:marker-style-name="T1"/>
   <table:table table:name="Table1" table:style-name="Table1">
    <table:table-column table:style-name="Table1.A"/>
    <table:table-column table:style-name="Table1.B"/>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="Table1.1">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="Table1.A1" office:value-type="string">
      <text:p text:style-name="P1" loext:marker-style-name="T1"><text:span text:style-name="T1">Burney Falls &amp; Creek – 21 species</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T1"/></text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="Table1.A1" office:value-type="string">
      <text:p text:style-name="P1" loext:marker-style-name="T1"><text:span text:style-name="T1">Lake Britton – 22 Species</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T1"/></text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="Table1.1">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="Table1.A1" office:value-type="string">
      <text:p text:style-name="P1" loext:marker-style-name="T1"><text:span text:style-name="T1">Common Merganser  1<text:line-break/>Band-tailed Pigeon  1<text:line-break/>Black Swift  6<text:line-break/>Anna&apos;s Hummingbird  2<text:line-break/>Turkey Vulture  3<text:line-break/>Osprey  1<text:line-break/>Acorn Woodpecker  3<text:line-break/>Downy Woodpecker  1<text:line-break/>Hairy Woodpecker  2<text:line-break/>Western Warbling Vireo  1<text:line-break/>Mountain Chickadee  4<text:line-break/>Tree Swallow  4<text:line-break/>Brown Creeper  3<text:line-break/>Purple Finch  1<text:line-break/>Dark-eyed Junco  2<text:line-break/>Song Sparrow  3<text:line-break/>Brown-headed Cowbird  5<text:line-break/>Yellow-rumped Warbler  2<text:line-break/>Hermit Warbler  2<text:line-break/>Western Tanager  3<text:line-break/>Black-headed Grosbeak  2     </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T1"/></text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="Table1.A1" office:value-type="string">
      <text:p text:style-name="P1" loext:marker-style-name="T1"><text:span text:style-name="T3">Canada Goose  2<text:line-break/>Killdeer  1<text:line-break/>Western Grebe  6<text:line-break/>Great Blue Heron  1<text:line-break/>Turkey Vulture  3<text:line-break/>Osprey  1<text:line-break/>Bald Eagle  1<text:line-break/>Belted Kingfisher  1<text:line-break/>Pileated Woodpecker  1<text:line-break/>Northern Flicker (Red-shafted)  1<text:line-break/>Western Wood-Pewee  1<text:line-break/>Western Flycatcher  1<text:line-break/>Black Phoebe  1<text:line-break/>Steller&apos;s Jay  1<text:line-break/>Common Raven  1<text:line-break/>Tree Swallow  8<text:line-break/>Barn Swallow  6<text:line-break/>European Starling  2<text:line-break/>American Robin  4<text:line-break/>Song Sparrow  2<text:line-break/>Bullock&apos;s Oriole  1     HO<text:line-break/>Brewer&apos;s Blackbird  3</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T4"/></text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
    </table:table-row>
   </table:table>
   <text:section text:style-name="Sect1" text:name="TextSection">
    <text:p text:style-name="P2" loext:marker-style-name="T1"><text:span text:style-name="T1">While the swifts were flying high over the falls and creek, many of the birds were quite close: <text:s/>The osprey sitting on a tree limb, 20 feet from Fisherman’s Bridge at eye level. The Piliated Woodpecker who flew into a tree on the edge of the upper Lake Britton parking lot and stayed for a while. <text:s/>And farther away, seen with binoculars: The Blue Heron standing motionless on a log across the lagoon from the boat ramp. <text:s/>The Western Grebes floating mid lake. And, of course, the tree and barn swallows swooping over the fishing pier. <text:s/>Grab your binoculars next time you are there….and come see who’s here at the park.</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T1"/></text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="P3" loext:marker-style-name="T1"/>
    <text:p text:style-name="P2" loext:marker-style-name="T1"><text:soft-page-break/><text:span text:style-name="T1"><text:line-break/><text:line-break/></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T1"/></text:p>
    <text:p text:style-name="Standard"/>
   </text:section>
  </office:text>
 </office:body>
</office:document>